item.title: CVE-2018-3921|2024-09-16T18:23:27.563Z -- computerinsel -- computerinsel%20photoline
item.description: A memory corruption vulnerability exists in the PSD-parsing functionality of Computerinsel Photoline 20.54. A specially crafted PSD image processed via the application can lead to a stack overflow, overwriting arbitrary data. An attacker can deliver a PSD image to trigger this vulnerability and gain code execution.
